<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="8" MadCap:lastHeight="319" MadCap:lastWidth="614" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare,Products.Pulse" MadCap:fileTags="Pulse/PulseTopicAuthor.Kate">
    <body>
        <ol class="LowerAlpha">
            <li>In the <span class="Emphasis">Name</span> field, type a group name.</li>
            <li>In the  <span class="Emphasis">Description</span> field, type a short group description.</li>
            <li>
                <p>In the <span class="Emphasis">Audience</span> field, select the desired audience. These settings correspond to the membership group permissions. </p>
                <ul class="FirstLevel">
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Employees</span> Members of the Employees group can be invited to and join groups.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Employees and Customers</span> Members of both the Employees and Customers groups can be invited to and join groups.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>(Optional) Place a check mark in the <span class="Emphasis">Moderation</span> box if you want all group posts to be approved by a moderator before being displayed.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive,FlareGuides.FlarePulseGuide"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Pulse/Moderation/Moderating_Posts.htm">Moderating (Approving/Rejecting) Posts</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
            <li>(Optional) Place a check mark in the <span class="Emphasis">Visibility</span> box. The group will be visible to users who perform a search for the group. If the check box is left blank, users must be invited to join the group. </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>